00005000                            	include "src/engine_menu_core.asm"
00005000                            ; ======================================================================
00005000                            ; src/engine_menu_core.asm
00005000                            ; ROM range: 0x005000-0x01FFFF - early engine and menu/core gameplay logic
00005000                            ; ======================================================================
00005000                            ; Early engine/core body kept mostly opaque until routine boundaries are mapped.
00005000                            ; The front of this file continues the task/input helper chain that begins at `0x004FEE`
00005000                            ; in `src/vblank_tasks.asm`. The `0x005016-0x00505C` helpers currently look like a compact
00005000                            ; input-sequence stream built from (duration,value) byte pairs in `0xFF1400`, reusing
00005000                            ; the selected-input mirror at `0x8A7A-0x8A7D` as playback state. The bootstrap
00005000                            ; display-setup stub at `0x005170-0x0051C5` and the controller-read helpers at
00005000                            ; `0x0051C6-0x005260` are now source-authored in ROM order. A later recovered clue at
00005000                            ; `0x00805A-0x0083CF` now strongly points at the inventory/equipment menu UI: the code
00005000                            ; repeat-gates selected input, blinks the main cursor plus scroll arrows, redraws the
00005000                            ; four-row visible window, and references the inline heading strings `SELECT`,
00005000                            ; `WEAPON`, `ARMOR`, `SHIELD`, `BOOTS`, `ITEM`, and `MAGIC`. The adjacent
00005000                            ; `0x0083D0-0x00861E` continuation now also looks like the same menu/status panel: it
00005000                            ; redraws the visible four-row list, formats decimal values, carries inline `AP`, `DP`,
00005000                            ; `SP`, and `GOLD` strings, and now also draws a likely level readout plus the live gold
00005000                            ; total. The newly source-authored upstream slice at `0x007924-0x007A43` now looks like
00005000                            ; the paired horizontal-toggle owner plus loop body for the adjacent magic/status submode:
00005000                            ; it watches the left/right bits in repeat-gated input `0x95D9`, flips bit 0 of `0x9606`,
00005000                            ; picks one of two top-row tile ids from the tiny table at `0x00799A`, and refreshes the
00005000                            ; nearby status graphics through `0x008620` / `0x00863C` while `0x95E0` / `0x95E4` act
00005000                            ; like a modal flag plus saved selection backup. An external text dump also confirms the
00005000                            ; localized spell names `FIRE STORM`, `QUAKE`, `THUNDER`, `POWER`, `SHIELD`, and `RETURN`,
00005000                            ; plus nearby Wonder Boy strings such as `Oasis Boots`, `Fire-Urn`, `Purapril`, `Childam`,
00005000                            ; `Shiela Purapril`, `Prince of the Devil World`, and `Bio-Mecha`; however, the explicit
00005000                            ; heading bytes at `0x0082C4-0x0082EC` still take precedence over flattened dump lines when
00005000                            ; the two disagree. The next recovered slice at `0x007A44-0x007BA9` now shows the same
00005000                            ; submode can commit one of two cached selector values back into an entry, redraw a small
00005000                            ; 12-slot grid of menu entries, and refresh a compact adjacent status panel whose scratch
00005000                            ; bytes live around `0x959C`, `0x95EE`, `0x95F0`, and `0x9654`. The newly source-authored
00005000                            ; continuation at `0x007BAA-0x007CA3` also proves the next rows are a six-spell magic-grid
00005000                            ; redraw: it stores localized row records for `FIRE STORM`, `QUAKE`, `THUNDER`, `POWER`,
00005000                            ; `SHIELD`, and `RETURN`, highlights the two spell ids mirrored in `0x9F10/0x9F11`, and
00005000                            ; reuses `0x95B7` / `0x95C8` as empty/filled tile counts for a paired two-row spell bar.
00005000                            ; The broader engine body still stays opaque around the higher-level owners that seed the
00005000                            ; category descriptor and status values. Raw ROM work on the next incbin-backed
00005000                            ; The next source-authored bridge at `0x00882C-0x0088C1` now normalizes a candidate
00005000                            ; magic/status id before clearing matching top-row assignments in `0x9F10/0x9F11`, then
00005000                            ; consumes the pending packed gauge target at `0x9628`, chooses one of two scale/table
00005000                            ; bundles, clamps against the current packed value at `0x9602/0x9604`, and dispatches into
00005000                            ; the now source-authored three-row tile-strip writer at `0x0088D6`. The later
00005000                            ; `0x008A04-0x008C33` continuation is now also source-authored as the same spell-bar refill,
00005000                            ; gauge-tile upload, and layout-width synthesis rooted in `0x95AA`, `0x95B8-0x95C3`, and
00005000                            ; `0x95F4/0x95F6`.
00005000                            ; The newly source-authored tail at `0x008C34-0x008C7F` snapshots the local magic-menu
00005000                            ; selection scratch, resets list/cursor/scroll state, and captures top-row selector bytes
00005000                            ; from `0x9F10/0x9F11` when they still point at the lower magic/status row. The exact
00005000                            ; game-facing stat meaning of the gauge itself still needs more evidence, so the remaining
00005000                            ; scale bundles and downstream render/upload path stay incbin-backed for now. The
00005000                            ; newly source-authored bridge at
00005000                            ; `0x007D9C-0x008059` now links that magic/status flow back into the generic visible-list
00005000                            ; inventory UI: it confirms visible entries, blinks the selected row, queues menu-text row
00005000                            ; transfers through `0x8A77`, shows an inline `PAUSE` prompt, and expands packed 32-tile row
00005000                            ; templates before the already-authored repeat helper resumes at `0x00805A`.
00005000                            
